WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.140
Chapter 6 of Proverbs. King James Version. This LibriVox recording is in the public domain.

00:06.600 --> 00:15.740
Recording by Michael Packard. My son, if thou be surety for thy friend, if thou hast stricken thy hand with a stranger,

00:16.620 --> 00:22.600
thou art snared with the words of thy mouth, thou art taken with the words of thy mouth.

00:23.640 --> 00:30.360
Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself. When thou art come into the hand of thy friend, go,

00:30.820 --> 00:39.120
humble thyself, and make sure thy friend. Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids.

00:40.120 --> 00:47.100
Deliver thyself as a roe from the hand of the hunter, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.

00:47.480 --> 00:56.000
Go to the aunt thou sluggard, consider her ways, and be wise. Which, having no guide, overseer, or ruler,

00:56.520 --> 01:03.300
provideth her meat in the summer, and gathereth her food in the harvest. How long wilt thou sleep,

01:03.360 --> 01:11.060
O sluggard? When wilt thou arise out of thy sleep? Yet a little sleep, a little slumber,

01:11.060 --> 01:18.100
a little folding of the hands to sleep. So shall thy poverty come as one that travaileth,

01:18.640 --> 01:27.160
and thy want as an armed man. A naughty person, a wicked man, walketh with a foward mouth. He

01:27.160 --> 01:41.040
winketh with his eyes, he speaketh with his feet, he teacheth with his fingers. Fowardness is in his

01:41.040 --> 01:49.020
calamity come suddenly. Suddenly shall he be broken without remedy. These six things doth the

01:49.020 --> 01:58.840
Lord hate, yea, seven are an abomination unto him. A proud look, a lying tongue, and hands that shed

01:58.840 --> 02:07.160
innocent blood, and heart that deviseth wicked imaginations, feet that be swift in running to

02:07.160 --> 02:14.180
mischief, a false witness that speaketh lies, and he that soweth discord among brethren.

02:14.880 --> 02:22.260
My son, keep thy father's commandment, and forsake not the law of thy mother. Bind them

02:22.260 --> 02:28.600
continually upon thine heart, and tie them about thy neck. When thou goest it shall lead thee,

02:28.760 --> 02:35.500
when thou sleepest it shall keep thee, and when thou awakest it shall talk with thee. For the

02:35.500 --> 02:43.000
commandment is a lamp, and the law is light, and reproofs of instruction are the way of life. To

02:43.000 --> 02:50.640
keep thee from the evil woman, from the flattery of the tongue of a strange woman. Lest not after

02:50.640 --> 02:57.360
her beauty in thine heart, neither let her take thee with her eyelids. For by means of a horish

02:57.360 --> 03:03.640
woman a man is brought to a piece of bread, and the adulteress will hunt for the precious life.

03:03.640 --> 03:13.320
Can a man take fire in his bosom, and his clothes not be burned? Can one go upon hot coals, and his

03:13.320 --> 03:21.560
feet not be burned? So he that goeth into his neighbor's wife, whosoever toucheth her, shall

03:21.560 --> 03:28.460
not be innocent. Men do not despise a thief if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry.

03:28.460 --> 03:36.280
But if he be found, he shall restore sevenfold, he shall give all the substance of his house.

03:37.080 --> 03:42.800
But whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding, he that doeth it destroyeth his

03:42.800 --> 03:52.240
own soul. A wound and dishonor shall he get, and his reproach shall not be wiped away. For jealousy

03:52.240 --> 04:00.520
is the rage of a man, therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance. He will not regard any

04:00.520 --> 04:06.160
ransom, neither will he rest content, though thou givest many gifts.

